"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The roc_auc_score function in scikit-learn expects the true labels to be binary (0 or 1) and the predicted scores to be the probability of the positive class. However, in this case, the true labels are all 1, which means there is no negative class. The roc_auc_score function will throw an error in this case because it cannot calculate the AUC-ROC score without a negative class.\", \"patch\": \"4c4\\n< true_labels = np.array([1, 1, 1])\\n---\\n> true_labels = np.array([1, 0, 1])\\n\"}"